{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f292d8cc-74aa-436c-b4a8-86b47a051633","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `*.csproj`** — change the target framework:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\n**Then rebuild & test:**\n```bash\ndotnet restore\ndotnet build\ndotnet test   # if you have tests\n```\n\nAlso check for any NuGet packages with version-specific references (e.g., `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*` or `Microsoft.Extensions.*`) and update those to their .NET 11-compatible versions. Run `dotnet list package --outdated` to find them.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"637a73f0-ae97-4395-9175-dc6f060de12e","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no need to explore their codebase since they've described the files involved.","outputTokens":306,"requestId":"D401:1A381E:24D37C0:27F30A2:69FBB8E0"},"id":"8f25d528-20a7-4c7e-aeee-74678c9e7e15","timestamp":"2026-05-06T21:55:54.028Z","parentId":"d50b0c88-4df0-4c4f-a02d-9b3aed4270ad"}
